RptMPRProjectList.Name: Prevention and Control of Hepatitis in Punjab
RptMPRProjectList.IssueRemarks:
Progress 2019-20:
 
  • 132 Hepatitis Clinics established
  • 81,929 HCV patients treated
  • 7320 HBV patients treated
  • Ongoing Hepatitis B vaccination: 444,495 vaccinated
  • Diagnostic framework relevant to the program: Upgradation of Central Hepatitis Lab for Covid-19 testing (100% completed)
  • Hepatitis Rules 2019 approved by the Cabinet 
  • Transition from Semi-DAA based regimen (Sofosbuvir + Ribavirin)to Full DAA Regimen (Sofosbuvir + Daclatasvir)
  • 39 Million AD Syringes supplied from WHO pre-qualified suppliers to Primary & Secondary Healthcare Facilities
  • Procurement and administration of 1.5 Million Birth doses of HBV Vaccine across Punjab in Primary & Secondary Healthcare Facilities
  • Micro-elimination Project in High Prevalent Districts
  • Special initiative for Hepatitis free universities and madrissas
  • Public-private partnership with private sector hospitals and NGOs
  • Covid-19 PCR Testing in Hepatitis PCR Lab. Total 191,884 tests done
 
PC-I Status:
 
  • PC-I has been approved by PDWP with Gestation period till June 2022. Revised A.A issued.
 
Funds Utilization Plan:
 
  • Rs. 340 million for procurement of Hepatitis B&C RDTs and consumables (RFP completed, Purchase Order to be issued by 15th February).
